<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-08-14T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-08-14T09:00:00-05:00" n="583" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d583">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">611.5231/1014: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Bowers</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-08-14T14:00:00+00:00">August 14, 1935—2
                                        p.m.</date><lb/>[Received August 14—12:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>53. Exchange Control Board informed local banks August 12 that it
                                will, upon application, insure against exchange fluctuations amounts
                                covered by exchange applications in payments of imports from
                                England, France, Switzerland and Holland. Unless exchange insurance
                                extended to imports from the United States it might prejudice our
                                trade in favor of above countries. I have appointment with
                                Sub-Secretary of State August 16 and will then cable full
                                report.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Bowers</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>